HEADWORD: Isagogics
<hw>I"sa*gog"ics</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Theol.)</fld>
<def>That part of theological science directly preliminary to actual
exegesis, or interpretation of the Scriptures.</def>⟦br⟧
